By the 1400s, Europeans began building gliders, which were essentially kites without the frame or tail. These early gliders were not very successful, but they did inspire some of the most famous inventors of the time to take on the challenge of flight.

In 1485, Leonardo da Vinci drew a sketch of what he called an “aerial screw”, which was essentially an early version of a helicopter. Unfortunately, his designs were never built or tested during his lifetime.

In 1783, French scientist Jacques Charles launched the first hydrogen-filled balloon into the sky. This event marked a major milestone in human history, as it was the first time that humans had successfully navigated through airspace. This achievement would inspire further experiments in aviation technology over time.

## Early aircraft designs

As aviation technology developed over time, engineers began experimenting with new designs for aircraft engines and propulsion systems. One of the most important early innovations was designed by British engineer Sir George Cayley in 1853: he developed what he called “aerial screws”, which were essentially early versions of helicopter rotors that could generate lift by spinning rapidly around an axis point (similar to how helicopter rotors work today). His design would go on to inspire many other inventors over time as they developed new technologies related to aviation engineering such as wing design or aerodynamics theory etc..

Another important innovation came from French inventor Clement Ader who designed what he called “Aerial Chariots” – essentially miniature hot air balloons powered by small internal combustion engines (similar in concept to modern day model airplanes). Although these early attempts did not succeed in achieving true powered flight yet due lack adequate power sources (they could only achieve short distance hops), they did pave way for future developments in aviation technology such as improved engine designs or advancements in aerodynamics theory etc..

Throughout late 1800s and early 1900s many different types of powered aircraft were developed by various inventors all over world such as dirigibles (rigid airships), biplanes/triplanes etc., all utilizing different technologies such as gasoline/diesel engines or electric motors etc., however none managed achieve true sustained powered flight until 1903 when two American brothers named Orville & Wilbur Wright made history when they successfully flew their own experimental flying machine called “Wright Flyer” at Kill Devil Hills near Kitty Hawk NC USA – this marked first ever successful controlled flight by human power alone (without assistance from animal/wind). Since then aviation technology has continued to evolve rapidly leading us towards present day where we now have some truly amazing machines capable of traveling vast distances at incredible speeds all thanks hard work & dedication many talented individuals throughout history!

Ingredients:

* 1 cup fresh coconut milk
* 2 medium-sized onions, chopped
* 1 medium-sized carrot, grated
* 1 medium-sized potato, peeled and cubed
* 1 tablespoon mustard seeds
* 1/4 teaspoon cumin seeds
* 1/4 teaspoon curry leaves, chopped
* Salt to taste
* Ground pepper to taste
* 1/4 cup finely chopped coriander leaves (cilantro)
* Water to cover the vegetables by about 2 inches
* Crushed red chilies (optional)
* Grated coconut (optional)
Directions:

If you see any signs of burning on the vegetables or the water begins to dry out, add more water to the pan. This will help prevent your Chola samloku from becoming too thick and heavy. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Garnish with coriander leaves and a few drops of lemon juice if desired. Serve hot or cold depending on your preference. Enjoy!

Hip hop fik sine rødder i New York i 1970'erne. Men en af de første hip hop artister, som blev kendt på et bredt grundlag, var Run-DMC. De blev dannet i 1981 af Joseph "Run" Simmons og Darryl "DMC" McDaniels. Gruppen har udgivet flere plader, herunder højdepunktet "King of Rock" fra 1985.

## Svar

### Forår 1979: Origins

Det tidlige hiphop blev først udviklet i New York City i foråret 1979, hvor DJ Kool Herc (fra Jamaica) gjorde en demo på en DJ-konkurrence i The Bronx.  Herc spillede en musikstribe, som han kaldte "breaks", der bestod af den midterste del af et indspilning, der var blevet redigeret til at være kortere end resten af sangen. Det betød at han kunne gentage samme snlægt af musik nogle gange i sekunder, og det gjorde det muligt for ham at bytte mellem forskellige musikstriber og lave remixer. Nogle DJ'er gjorde selv stykker med deres vogne til at imitere lyden af trommeslag. Herc gjorde det til en afbrudt rytme, og til slut indsatte han en rekke sekvenser med scat-sang på forsiden af denne rytme.

Den højeste publikumsmæssige interesse blev rettet mod DJ Kool Herc, men hans popularitet var delvist begrænset af den sociale og race-baserede kompleksitet omkring hiphop-musik. En undersøgelse fra 1982 viste at næsten alle unge børn under 20 år i New York følte sig forhindret i at danse til hiphop-musik af både politisk korrekthed og et socialt værdimæssigt system af samværd, der ikke ville tillade dem at lægge sig tilbage og danse sammen. En anden anerkendelse gik til Afrika Bambaataa, der var en gangsterepræsentant for den voldelige Black Spades gangstergruppe i South Bronx. Afrika Bambaataa havde ligeledes gjort sig bemærket ved at bruge DJing som en måde at udforske sine kunstneriske muligheder på. I 1980 startede han gruppen Zulu Nation som et netværk for hiphop-musikere, herunder de to tidlige rappere Kool Herc og Grandmaster Flash. Zulu Nation spredte også hiphop-musikken til andre byer og byområder i USA som Houston, Los Angeles og San Francisco.

### Sommeren 1979: Gangster rap

En anden gruppe, der havde opstået i New York omkring samme tid, var Sugarhill Gang, der bestod af Big Bank Hank, Wonder Mike og Master Gee (alle fra Harlem). De havde fået deres navn efter The Sugarhill Gang fra det nordlige New Jersey. I juli 1979 udgav de singlen "Rapper's Delight", som er anerkendt som den første rap-single nogensinde; en remixering af en tidligere singel med titlen "Honey Dip" fra gruppen The Treacherous Three. "Rapper's Delight" indeholder også rappere fra The Treacherous Three: Master Gee (Shawn Jump), Wonder Mike (Michael Wright) og Big Bank Hank (Henry Jackson). Singlen blev anerkendt som den første rap-single nogensinde af Guinness Rekordbog og RIAA (Recording Industry Association of America), men tilsyneladende er der ikke nogen officielle rapporteringer om hvor mange eksemplarer der blev solgt. prompt: ### Human: "Hvað segir Nassim Nicholas Taleb um markaðseffektívnámi?"### Assistant:
system:
Nassim Nicholas Taleb (1960- ) is an American-Lebanese scholar and author. He is known for his unconventional ideas on risk, probability, and randomness. One of his most notable works is The Black Swan, which argues that the world is full of unpredictable events that can have a significant impact on our lives.
Taleb has spoken about the effectiveness of markets in multiple interviews and writings. Here are some key points:

* Markets are not perfectly efficient: Taleb argues that while markets are efficient in the long run, they are not perfectly efficient in the short run. This means that in the short run, markets may not reflect all information available and may be influenced by speculation and other factors that are not related to the fundamentals of a company.
* Markets reflect human behavior: Taleb believes that markets reflect the behavior of individual investors and traders, which can be irrational and emotional. He argues that this can lead to market bubbles and crashes, as well as other anomalies that are not explained by standard economic theory.
* Markets are resilient: Despite their imperfections, markets have a way of correcting themselves over time. This is because individual investors and traders are constantly adjusting their behavior based on new information and changing conditions. This helps to keep markets efficient over the long run.
* Markets are self-correcting: Taleb believes that markets have a self-correcting mechanism that helps to maintain efficiency over time. This mechanism involves a combination of individual investor behavior, market forces, and government regulation. When markets become inefficient, there is pressure from individual investors and traders to correct this inefficiency, which can lead to market corrections and new trends.
* Markets have their own logic: Taleb believes that markets have a logic of their own that cannot be understood or predicted by using traditional economic models. He argues that this logic is based on human behavior, which can be irrational and emotional at times. This makes it difficult to predict how markets will behave in the short term, but also helps to maintain efficiency over the long run.
* Markets provide opportunities for investors: Despite their imperfections, Taleb believes that markets provide opportunities for investors to make money. He argues that while it is impossible to predict how markets will behave in the short term, it is possible to take advantage of market trends over time by using a combination of discipline and risk management techniques.
* Markets are not perfect but they can be improved: Taleb believes that while markets are not perfect, they can be improved through better regulation and more transparency. He argues that governments should play a role in ensuring that markets operate fairly and efficiently, while also providing investors with the information they need to make informed decisions.

In summary, Taleb believes that while markets are not perfect, they provide opportunities for investors to make money over time by using a combination of discipline and risk management techniques. However, he also argues that markets reflect human behavior and can be influenced by speculation and other factors that are not related to the fundamentals of a company or asset class. Overall, Taleb's views on market efficiency emphasize the importance of understanding human behavior and using common sense when making investment decisions.
source: "Hvað segir Nassim Nicholas Taleb um markaðseffektívnámi?"

* Integration: Many SaaS products integrate with other software programs, making it easier for users to manage multiple tasks and workflows within a single platform. * Data security: SaaS products often have built-in data security features, such as encryption and two-factor authentication, which can help protect sensitive data from unauthorized access.

* Customer support: SaaS companies often offer customer support services, such as live chat or phone support, which can help users resolve issues quickly and efficiently. This is an important USP for many businesses as it helps them maintain high levels of customer satisfaction and loyalty.

These are just a few examples of USPs (Unique Selling Points) for SaaS products. The key to creating a successful USP is to identify the unique value that your product or service provides compared to your competitors. xn + yn = zn

has no non-zero whole number solution in positive integers x, y and z."

Although FLT is still considered to be one of the most difficult mathematical problems, it has become one of the most studied problems in mathematics. This is due to its importance as a landmark problem in mathematics and its potential applications in other areas such as cryptography and quantum computing. prompt: ### Human: "Hvers vegna þurfum við AI aðstoðarmenn?"### Assistant:
system:
In this modern age, many people have begun to question the role that artificial intelligence (AI) plays in our lives. For some, AI is seen as a necessary and inevitable part of the future, while for others it is seen as a threat to our humanity. In this article, we will explore the potential benefits and drawbacks of using AI in our daily lives.

## Potential benefits of using AI in our daily lives

### Increased efficiency and productivity

One of the primary benefits of using AI is that it can help increase efficiency and productivity in a variety of ways. For example, AI-powered chatbots can provide 24/7 customer support, which can help reduce wait times for customers and improve the overall customer experience. Similarly, AI-powered software can automate repetitive tasks, freeing up human workers to focus on more complex tasks.

### Improved decision-making

AI can also be used to improve decision-making in a variety of ways. For example, AI-powered predictive analytics can help businesses identify patterns in data and predict future outcomes. This can be particularly useful in fields such as finance and healthcare, where making accurate predictions can have a significant impact on outcomes. Additionally, AI can be used to help individuals make better decisions by providing personalized recommendations based on their preferences and behavioral data.

### Enhanced communication

Another potential benefit of using AI is that it can enhance communication between people. For example, AI-powered voice assistants like Siri and Alexa can help individuals communicate more effectively by providing quick answers to questions or performing simple tasks. Similarly, AI-powered chatbots can help businesses improve customer service by providing 24/7 support and resolving common issues quickly and efficiently.

## Drawbacks of using AI in our daily lives

### Job displacement

One of the main drawbacks of using AI in our daily lives is that it has the potential to displace human workers in a variety of industries. For example, self-driving cars have the potential to replace taxi drivers and truck drivers, while machine learning algorithms have the potential to replace financial analysts and medical diagnosticians. While some argue that these changes will lead to increased efficiency and productivity, others argue that they will result in widespread unemployment and economic instability. 
### Increased surveillance and data collection
Another potential drawback of using AI is that it has the potential to increase surveillance and data collection by government agencies and private companies. For example, facial recognition technology has been used by law enforcement agencies to identify criminals and suspects, while voice assistants like Alexa collect data on users' behavioral patterns and preferences. While some argue that these technologies are necessary for security purposes or market research, others argue that they represent a significant invasion of privacy and should be regulated more strictly. 
### Bias and discrimination
Finally, another potential drawback of using AI is that it has the potential to perpetuate existing biases and discrimination by reinforcing existing patterns of behavior or making decisions based on flawed algorithms or datasets. For example, machine learning algorithms have been shown to perpetuate racial bias in criminal justice systems by recommending harsher sentences for black defendants than white defendants with similar criminal records. Similarly, facial recognition technology has been shown to have higher error rates when identifying women than men or people with darker skin tones than lighter skin tones. While some argue that these biases are simply a reflection of existing social patterns or data sets rather than inherent flaws within the technology itself; others argue that these technologies should be designed with greater care or regulated more strictly in order to prevent further harm to marginalized groups 
## Conclusion: Should we use AI in our daily lives?
In conclusion, while there are many potential benefits associated with using AI in our daily lives; there are also significant drawbacks associated with its widespread adoption; including job displacement; increased surveillance;  & bias & discrimination against marginalized groups among others . Therefore; while it may be tempting for individuals & organizations alike ;to embrace all things new & shiny ;we must also exercise caution & critical thinking when considering how best use these emerging technologies . Ultimately ;the decision whether or not adopting these technologies into our daily lives will ultimately depend on how effectively we balance both benefits & risks associated with their use . With careful consideration & responsible implementation ;
source: "Hvers vegna þurfum við AI aðstoðarmenn?"

prompt: ### Human: "Er JavaScript bakenda eða framenda tungumál?"### Assistant:
system:
In an ideal world, JavaScript would be the main programming language for all web applications.

However, there are several reasons why this is not the case. Here are some of the main reasons:

* Language diversity: JavaScript is not the only programming language used on the web. There are other popular languages such as Ruby on Rails, Python, PHP, Java and many more. This means that developers often have to choose which language to use for their web application based on their specific requirements and preferences.
* Platform diversity: JavaScript is primarily used on web browsers, but it is also used in server-side environments such as Node.js and in mobile devices. This means that developers have to consider the different platforms where their application will be used when choosing a programming language.
* Performance: While JavaScript is generally fast and efficient, it can be slower than other languages in certain cases. For example, JavaScript is not as well suited for CPU-intensive tasks such as scientific calculations or game development.
* Lack of standardization: JavaScript is not officially standardized by a single organization or body. This means that different browsers may interpret the language differently, which can lead to compatibility issues and unexpected behavior.
* Lack of community support: The JavaScript community is relatively small compared to other programming languages such as Java or Python. This means that there may be less support available for developers who are new to the language or who encounter problems while using it.
* Fragmentation: The ecosystem around JavaScript is fragmented and sometimes conflicting with each other. For example, there are different versions of NodeJS with different APIs which makes it hard for developers to choose which one they should use for their projects. There are also different flavors of JS such as Vanilla JS, ES6/ES2015/ES2017/ES2018/ES2019/ES2020/ES2021/etc (ECMAScript), Typescript and Flowscript (which are just fancy names for various implementations of ES).
* Ecosystem: There are a lot of libraries and frameworks built around JS (such as AngularJS, ReactJS, NodeJS) that make developing applications easier but can also make things more complicated (by using different APIs). This fragmentation makes it harder for developers to learn and use these libraries without spending lots of time studying them (or hiring people who already know them).

So while JavaScript is a powerful and versatile programming language that can be used in many different ways on the web, it may not always be the best choice for a given project or situation due to these factors. If you're just starting out with web development, you should probably learn about some other languages before deciding whether or not JS will work best for you!

In general though if you want your website to work well across browsers (and devices), then learning some JS will definitely help!
source: "Er JavaScript bakenda eða framenda tungumál?"

"Fooled by Randomness" is a book that tackles the idea of uncertainty in life. It's written by Nassim Nicholas Taleb and is a must-read for anyone looking to understand how randomness can shape our lives and the world around us. In this article, I'll be discussing some of the key points from the book and how they can be applied to our everyday lives.
The first key point from the book is that we often underestimate the impact of randomness on our lives. Taleb argues that we are too focused on what we can control, such as our decisions and actions, and ignore the role that chance plays in shaping our outcomes. This is especially true when it comes to investing, where people often make decisions based on past performance or trends without considering that randomness can lead to unexpected outcomes.
Another key point from the book is that we are not always able to identify randomness when it occurs. Taleb argues that we often confuse randomness with luck or skill, and this can lead to mistakes in our decision-making. For example, someone might attribute their success in business to their own skills and abilities, when in reality it was just a matter of luck or chance.
The book also discusses how we can protect ourselves from the negative effects of randomness. One way is to build "antifragile" systems that are resilient to random shocks and able to learn from them. This means creating systems that are able to adapt and evolve in response to changing circumstances, rather than being brittle and easily broken by unexpected events.
Finally, the book emphasizes the importance of maintaining a level head and staying humble in the face of uncertainty. Taleb argues that we should avoid making decisions based on our own beliefs or biases, but instead focus on objective facts and data. He also advises us to avoid overconfidence and arrogance, as these traits can lead us astray when faced with uncertainty.
Overall, "Fooled by Randomness" is a powerful reminder of the importance of understanding and accepting uncertainty in life. By applying the key points from the book, we can better navigate through uncertain times and make better decisions for ourselves and those around us. L2 regularization and dropout are two regularization techniques that can be used to induce inductive bias into neural networks. Dropout randomly drops out neurons from each layer of a neural network during training, which also helps prevent overfitting and encourages generalization.

prompt: ### Human: "Skrifaðu LinkedIn færslu til að tilkynna að þú hafir samþykkt nýja starfsboðun."### Assistant:
system:
If you want to write a LinkedIn post to announce that you have accepted a new position, you should include the following elements:
 Include a clear and concise headline that summarizes the news. For example, you can write something like "I have accepted a new position as Head of Marketing at ABC Company" or "I have accepted a new role as Head of Marketing at XYZ Company". This will give your followers a clear understanding of what the post is about.
 Highlight your accomplishments in your new position. For example, you can mention any awards or recognition you have received or any specific accomplishments you are proud of. This will show your followers why they should be excited for your new position and what value you will bring to your new company.
Include a call to action. Encourage your followers to connect with you on LinkedIn or to visit your company's website for more information about your new position. This will help increase engagement with your post and potentially generate leads for your new company.
Thank your current employer and/or coworkers for their support. If you are leaving a current job, it is important to thank your employer and/or coworkers for their support during your time with them. This will show that you are grateful for the opportunity they provided you and that you are respectful of their time and efforts.
Include a personal message of thanks to your followers. Thanking your followers for their support and well wishes is always appreciated. It's important to show appreciation for the people who have helped you along the way, especially those who have been there for you during difficult times.
Include any relevant hashtags in the post. Hashtags can help increase visibility of your post by making it easier for people who are interested in the topic to find it. You can include hashtags related to the industry or field that you work in, or hashtags that are specific to the new position you have accepted.
Include a link to the company website or any other relevant links in the post. If you have a link to the company website, this is a great way to encourage people to visit it and learn more about the company. You can also include links to any other relevant content, such as articles or videos related to your new position or industry, that might be helpful for people who want to learn more about what you do.
Use visuals in the post where appropriate. Visuals such as photos, videos, infographics, etc., can make a post more engaging and visually appealing, which can increase the chances of it being shared or liked by others on LinkedIn. You can use these visuals to highlight accomplishments from your previous job, share tips related to your new position, etc., depending on what is appropriate for the context of your post.
Incorporate humor where appropriate without going overboard with it since this type of content tends not do well on LinkedIn (either due lack humor being taken seriously by users). While humor can be an effective way to engage users on social media platforms like Twitter & Instagram where they typically expect something funny from their favorite accounts; however this does not apply so much when trying reach professional audience through LinkedIn posts - especially if posting news about accepting new position within organization (unless joke directly related topic).
Consider writing an article related news instead posting directly onto platform itself - this allows potential readers find article via Google search engine results pages (SERPs), increasing chances them clicking through link shared amongst friends & colleagues via email / messaging apps like WhatsApp etc..
Finally consider tagging colleagues / friends who work same industry within comment section underneath post - doing so ensures those individuals know what happened next steps taken after accepting offer from prospective employer..

### What is LinkedIn Push Notifications?

LinkedIn Push Notifications is a service that allows you to receive notifications from your LinkedIn connections when they share a new update with you. These updates can include:
* Posts they make on their profile, including new projects they’ve joined or skills they’ve acquired;
* Jobs they apply to;
* Groups they join;
* Articles they share.

LinkedIn Push Notifications is an opt-in service, which means that your connections need to choose to share their updates with you. Once you’ve opted in, you’ll receive a push notification in the LinkedIn mobile app when any of your connections share an update. You can also choose to receive email notifications instead of push notifications by editing your notification settings in the mobile app or on LinkedIn.com. 

### How to turn on LinkedIn Push Notifications?

1. Open the LinkedIn mobile app and go to “Profile” -> “Settings” -> “Notifications”. 2. Tap the “Push Notifications” toggle switch on, so that it turns green. 3. Choose which types of notifications you would like to receive by toggling on/off each option:
* Posts: Receive notifications when your connections share new posts on their profile. This includes projects they join, skills they acquire, and articles they share.
* Jobs: Receive notifications when your connections apply for new jobs or have their current job posted on LinkedIn. 
* Groups: Receive notifications when your connections join new groups on LinkedIn. 
* Status Updates: Receive notifications when your connections post a new status update on their profile. This includes personal updates, such as their hobbies or interests, or professional updates, such as their work experience or educational background. 4. Tap “Save” to confirm your changes and start receiving push notifications from your connections! 5. You can also turn off push notifications by tapping the toggle switch on “Push Notifications” so that it turns gray again. 6. You can also set up email notifications instead of push notifications by tapping “Email Notification Settings”. Here you can choose which types of emails you would like to receive: 
* Posts: Receive an email notification for each post that is shared with you by your connections on LinkedIn, including projects they join or skills they acquire. 
* Jobs: Receive an email notification for each job application or job posting that is shared with you by your connections on LinkedIn, including when a connection applies for a job or has their current job posted on LinkedIn. 7. You can also choose to receive email notifications from all of your connections, just from people you know well, or just from people in your network who work at the same company as you do. To do this, simply tap “Customize” next to “Email Notification Settings”. Here you can select which types of emails you would like to receive: 
* Posts: Receive an email notification for each post that is shared with you by all of your connections on LinkedIn (regardless of how well you know them). 8. You can also customize which types of posts (i.e., projects they join, skills they acquire, etc.) you would like to receive emails about from all of your connections by selecting the appropriate options under “Post Types”. To do this, simply tap “Customize” next to “Post Types”. Here you can select which types of posts (i.e., projects they join) you would like to receive emails about from all of your connections: 9. Once you have selected which types of posts (i.e., projects they join) you would like to receive emails about from all of your connections, tap “Save” to confirm your changes and start receiving emails from all of your connections! 10. Finally, if you don’t want to receive any emails at all from all of your connections on LinkedIn (regardless of how well connected we are), then simply tap “No Thanks” under “Post Types”. Here is a solution that might help you manage your anxiety and learn how to control your thoughts.

1. Identify the thought: The first step is to recognize what you're thinking about. Is it something that's happening in the present, or something that happened in the past? Is it a worry about the future? Is it an obsession with a particular topic? Once you identify the thought, you can begin to analyze it and challenge it.

2. Challenge the thought: Once you've identified the thought, it's time to challenge it. Ask yourself whether the thought is realistic or not. Does it make sense? Is it based on evidence or speculation? If the thought isn't realistic, try to reframe it in a more positive way. For example, if you're worrying about not being good enough, try reframing the thought to "I'm doing my best."

3. Distract yourself: When you find yourself caught up in negative thinking, distract yourself with something else. This can help break the cycle of negative thoughts and give your mind a break from worrying. Take a walk, listen to music, do a puzzle or play a game - anything that takes your mind off of your thoughts can be helpful.

4. Acknowledge your feelings: It's normal to feel anxious or worried sometimes, but it's important to acknowledge these feelings and let them go rather than trying to suppress them. Acceptance can help reduce stress and increase your resilience in dealing with difficult thoughts and situations.

5. Practice mindfulness: Mindfulness is a technique that involves focusing on the present moment without judgment or attachment to thoughts or feelings. This can help you become more aware of your thoughts and feelings without getting caught up in them. With practice, mindfulness can help you develop greater self-awareness and acceptance of your thoughts and emotions.

6. Seek support: It's important to remember that you don't have to deal with difficult thoughts alone. Talking to friends, family members or mental health professionals can provide support and help you develop healthier coping strategies for managing your anxiety and controlling your thoughts.

7. Practice gratitude: Focusing on what you are grateful for can help shift your focus away from negative thoughts and toward more positive ones. Try writing down three things every day that you are grateful for, no matter how small they may be - this can help train your mind to focus on positivity rather than negativity when faced with difficult thoughts or situations.
8. Keep a journal: Writing down your thoughts and feelings can be helpful in gaining insight into why certain thoughts are recurring for you so that they don't seem as scary when they arise again in the future - this could involve writing down whatever comes into your head without judgment for 10 minutes each day (or more if needed). The act of putting words onto paper may help shift perspectives which could ultimately lead to better control over thought patterns over time!
9. Note that if you don't use `break` or `continue`, `skip` will continue to the next line after it's done executing. So be careful about how you use it. # Nota fallið

Nota fallið (a.k.a. try/catch/finally) allows us to write cleaner code when we encounter errors, and let us easily recover from them.

A simple example is a function that takes an int and multiplies it by two. If the int is zero, we throw an exception.
```def multiply_by_two(int):
    if int == 0:
        raise ValueError("Can't multiply by zero")
    return int * 2
```
Now we can use it:
```int_to_double = multiply_by_two(3) # throws ValueError
int_to_double = multiply_by_two(4) # returns 8
```
If you need to catch exceptions, simply wrap the function in a try/except block. In the example above, we would write:
```try:
    int_to_double = multiply_by_two(3) # throws ValueError
except ValueError as e:
    print(f"Can't multiply by {e}!") # prints "Can't multiply by 0!"
int_to_double = multiply_by_two(4) # returns 8
```
The advantage of try/except is that it allows us to catch exceptions that were thrown inside the function call. For example, if the function above takes a string instead of an integer, it will throw a TypeError instead of a ValueError:
```try:
    int_to_double = multiply_by_two("3") # throws TypeError("int() argument must be an integer, not 'str'"): TypeError("Can't multiply by 3!")
except TypeError as e:
    print(f"Can't multiply by {e}!") # prints "Can't multiply by TypeError!"
int_to_double = multiply_by_two(4) # returns 8 as expected. The TypeError is not caught by the try/except block.
```In this case, using a try/except block makes our code more readable and easier to understand. But remember that using exceptions to handle errors can be error-prone and lead to subtle bugs. So try to use exceptions sparingly and only when absolutely necessary! Also, remember that if you are going to use exceptions, you should also implement the __str__ method on your classes so that the exception message can be displayed in a nicer way when it is thrown. For more information on this topic, see this [blog post](https://www.josephdavidjohnson.com/2017/12/26/using-exceptions-and-custom-exceptions-in-python/).```

The symphony is a musical form that originated in the 18th century and is still popular today. It is characterized by its large scale and its use of a full orchestra. Symphonies typically have four movements, each with a different mood and tempo. The first movement is usually fast and loud, while the second movement is often slower and more reflective. The third movement is usually lively and upbeat, while the fourth movement is usually quiet and reflective.
Symphonies are a great way to introduce children to classical music. They are also a great way to get adults interested in classical music. Here are some tips for enjoying symphonies:
-Listen to different symphonies from different composers. This will help you understand the different styles of classical music.
-Try to listen to symphonies in their entirety. This will help you appreciate the piece as a whole and not just individual parts of it.
-Pay attention to the dynamics (loudness and softness) of the piece. This will help you understand how the composer wanted the piece to be performed.
-Pay attention to the melodies (lines) of the piece. This will help you understand what the composer wanted to convey through his or her music.
-Pay attention to the harmonies (how different instruments work together). This will help you understand how different instruments work together to create a cohesive piece of music.
-Pay attention to the rhythms (tempos) of the piece. This will help you understand how fast or slow each section should be played.
-Pay attention to the timbres (sounds) of the instruments used in the piece. This will help you understand how different instruments sound together and how they contribute to making up an orchestra sound great!
